node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Yup That Exists on September 18, 2021. May be an image of emperor penguin and text that says 'YUP Yup That Exists @yup.that.exists Scientists find chemical from Venus in penguin feces, which could pertain to the origin of the species.'.

node.text:
Researchers from Imperial College London have just discovered an abnormal chemical in some samples of Penguin feces. The chemical is called phosphine, and it's rarely ever found on Earth, in fact, it's usually located 38 million miles away on a planet called Venus. 

The study is continuing on with further research at the moment, but researchers are excited to potentially get more information on the origins of Penguins. Including the potential outcome that they may have not originally been from this planet! 

Follow @yup.that.exists

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Yup That Exists on September 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YUP Yup That Exists @yup.that.exists Quantum gas experiment sets new record for coldest temperature, at 38 trillionths of a degree above absolute zero. -459.67 F'.

node.text:
Physicists at the University of Bremen, Germany have just produced the coldest temperature ever recorded thanks to their Quantum Gas experiment. Because Absolute Zero is impossible to acheive without zero atomic motion or kinetic energy in its atoms, the team of scientists managed to acheive a number very close... 38 trillionths of a degree above absolute zero.

Follow @yup.that.exists
